<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06053g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06053g">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06053g"> 53(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> openshirt 70 times</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">il est tr&egrave;s int&eacute;ressant de noter que chez les enfants l&apos;exercice de l&apos;attention se fait &agrave; l&apos;aide des jeux. &hellip; Ainsi l&apos;un des passe-temps favoris de l&apos;enfant, c&apos;est <mark>la r&eacute;p&eacute;tition multipli&eacute;e de la m&ecirc;me action</mark> (action de frapper, d&apos;ouvrir et de fermer, etc.). <font color="green">[It is very interesting to note that in children the exercise of attention is done using the games. ... Thus, one of the child&apos;s favorite pastimes is the multiplied repetition of the same action (action of hitting, opening and closing, etc.).]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 112</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
